article.headline: Elon 102, FDU-Florham 68
article.story: ELON, N.C. -- Josh Bonney scored 23 points and dished out nine assists to lead Elon to a convincing 102-68 win over Fairleigh Dickinson-Florham on Friday night. Drew Spradlin added 22 points and shot 3-for-7 from 3-point range for the Phoenix (2-2), and Devan Carter chipped in with 17 points and four steals. Elon used a 12-4 run in the first half to take a 36-22 lead after a 3-pointer from Carter with 6:32 remaining. The Phoenix led 52-32 at the half. A 12-1 run in the second half was capped by a layup by Chris Long with 5:19 left and put Elon up 95-57. Adam Katz finished with 20 points to lead the Devils (0-3). Elon shot 60.9 percent from the field (39-for-64). The Phoenix forced the Devils into 26 turnovers, including 16 steals. Elon also outrebounded FDU-Florham 29-24.
